reviewText: I love Patrick McGoohan's groundbreaking TV series The Prisoner and sort of thought it alone in its class, but no. Check out The Monitors, a mod mod 1960s surrealist spectacle about a decadent world invaded and conquered by a sort of cosmic neighborhood watch dressed in bowler hats. The Monitors assure peace and ask neither worship nor gratitude. And when our handsome hero and his rag tag gang get involved, we simultaneously get a zany adventure comedy and an incisive political analysis of the stress fractures developing in British society at the end of that trippy, trippy decade.
